チャニの迫力のあるダンス・リノの強弱あるダンス・ビニの力強いダンス・ヒョンジンの憑依型ダンス・ハニの余裕感あるダンス・リクスの体全身で大きく動くダンス・スンミンの適度に力の抜けているダンス・イエニの大人っぽさを感じるダンス。
この8人それぞれの個性をコンセプトやメッセージがちゃんと決まっている1曲で合わせるのは難しいことだし誰かにとっては自分の良さが魅せれないかもしれないのにスキズは、どんな曲だったとして8人全員の個性が死んでないしむしろ8人の個性が全部合わさった時、StrayKidsの曲は完成されている。

author: @clairruckman7674
text:
Yay! Back to fun dance (movement music, because cleaning even benefits from music like this.) 
I know likely just me but their ballad comeback just not for me. So excited to have this mini album. Things to bolster my play list. 
Also, wild idea, I'd love to see the agencies interwork now and again. It was what I loved with Kingdom. I remember the kid from BtoB when he got to work with other rappers, and you could see it inspired him and brought him some more modern things to try. I think it'd allow all groups to not get stuck in a well X formula worked lets keep doing exactly that. That works, but eventually nit dates the work.Not all bad, and stil things to love about it. Just saying from a creative stand point might help moral, and give the ability to elevate what all groups do. Plus, this might not be an entirely altruistic suggestion, because I'd love to see Stray Kids and Ateez work off each other again. Plus, from rap lines Id get more above 165 bpm music. It could also be done to fill out mini albums. Produce more sales if done correctly. Even if it is 1-3  songs of we did a cross over with these 3 groups, and our guys who obviously take the lead on their albums are featured with X groups idols. I.E. Stz, Ateez, and let's say BTS. If a Strat Kids album a rap song have Changbin, and Han, and Bang Chan take lead, but feature rappers from the other groups. 1 song added. If a BTS album have Namjoon, Jungkook, and my brain stopped working theur other, my preferred rapper from that group lead, but have like Changbin, and future album draw feature someone else popping in. The exact logistics might vary, but you get general gist. That would help sales for all groups imo, because I dont think just me that loves the sports day the groups have where they interact. 
I know highly competitive industry, and between labels, but hopefully if tried done might be a refresher for everyone. Just a chance to be a bit silly. The silliness is why I like JYP. It seems they are allowed more to try, and do lighter goofy stuff more often. 
But yay🎉 music that energizes me!

text: Stray Kids' choreography here showcases their seamless transitions and dynamic movement patterns that always enhance the energy of their performance. They maintain a fluid flow with natural transitions between sections to connect different movements. They don't stand in one formation to do a few moves then randomly rush to another formation to do another few moves with no apparent connection. I love how they are always synced precisely to the music's rhythm, and the sharp, synchronized group movements highlight the solo segments, making them visually deeelicious. You can't afford to blink you might miss something!!!

author: @Thalia8
text:
I’ve been watching Hyunjin fancams lately again and as a dancer, I want to say that Hyunjin is still one of the best male kpop dancer I have seen until this day (I've been to kpop since 1st gen). there are a lot of good kpop dancers as well, but HJ just hits different. his style is distinctive, his popping and locks are very sharp and on point. this guy can do ballet, jazz and contemporary as well. one of the best he got is his facial expressions whenever he dances. you can really see he is able to embody the song and dance it out. his footwork is also notable. I really want to see him dance personally. I think he is best because dance is not only about body control and how you move it it was considered as one of many ways to communicate with each other and that's what HJ does, he the definition of true dancer someone who controls his body and talks with his movements. 
what makes hyunjin very rare and special is that not only he is a professional dancer  with a perfect technique, he also has a deep connection with dance and passionate, he has the ability to tell a story through dance
